Download an OMOP Synthetic dataset.

downloadDataset.Rd

Download an OMOP Synthetic dataset.

Usage

downloadDataset(
  datasetName = "GiBleed",
  path = datasetsFolder(),
  overwrite = FALSE
)

Arguments

datasetName

Name of the dataset. See availableDatasets() for possibilities.

path

Path where to download the dataset.

overwrite

Whether to overwrite the dataset if it is already downloaded.

Value

The path to the downloaded dataset.

Examples

# \donttest{
library(OmopDatasets)

isDatasetDownloaded("GiBleed")
#> Error in isDatasetDownloaded("GiBleed"): ✖ Path
#>   /home/runner/work/OmopDatasets/OmopDatasets/docs/reference/OMOP_DATASETS does
#>   not exist.
downloadDataset("GiBleed")
#> Error in downloadDataset("GiBleed"): ✖ Path
#>   /home/runner/work/OmopDatasets/OmopDatasets/docs/reference/OMOP_DATASETS does
#>   not exist.
isDatasetDownloaded("GiBleed")
#> Error in isDatasetDownloaded("GiBleed"): ✖ Path
#>   /home/runner/work/OmopDatasets/OmopDatasets/docs/reference/OMOP_DATASETS does
#>   not exist.
# }
